.TH "__mcb_register_driver" 9 "__mcb_register_driver" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__mcb_register_driver \- Register a @mcb_driver at the system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __mcb_register_driver
.BI "(struct mcb_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "struct module *owner "  ","
.BI "const char *mod_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
The \fImcb_driver\fP
.IP "owner" 12
The \fImcb_driver\fP's module
.IP "mod_name" 12
The name of the \fImcb_driver\fP's module
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register a \fImcb_driver\fP at the system. Perform some sanity checks, if
the .probe and .remove methods are provided by the driver.
